        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 3:57PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 357 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 16 miles south of Ryegate to 17 miles
northwest of Laurel, or extending from 30 miles north of Columbus to
19 miles west of Billings, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Broadview, Comanche, Halfbreed Lake Wildlife, Hailstone Wildlife
Refuge and Rapelje.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
